  <p>Suppose that <tex>\bot</tex> was positive. The empty set <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left \{ \right \} \mathclose {}} \subseteq  A</tex> is semidirected and <tex>\bot \sqsubseteq   \bigsqcup { \mathopen {} \left \{ \right \} \mathclose {}} = \bot</tex>, but nonetheless <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left \{ \right \} \mathclose {}}</tex> is not inhabited.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25996</anchor> <rss>jms-002H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-002H</addr>  <route>jms-002H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The bottom element is not positive</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The bottom element <tex>\bot</tex> of a pointed dcpo <tex>A</tex> is not <link href="jms-001M.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001M" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo">positive</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
